HEADWORD: Carinaria
<hw>Car`i*na"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>carina</ets> keel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
oceanic heteropod Mollusca, having a thin, glassy, bonnet-shaped shell,
which covers only the nucleus and gills.</def>⟦br⟧
